# scripts/harness/lib/harness.env
#
# Template root Java package, expressed as a slash-separated path.
#
# Currently no hook consumes HARNESS_ROOT_PACKAGE: every check in
# scripts/harness/lib/hook-checks.sh uses fork-agnostic glob patterns like
# `*src/main/java/*.java` that match any forked package. The file is kept
# as a stub for future hooks that may need literal template-path matching,
# and as the documented rename point for forkers.
#
# If you fork this template and add a hook that matches literal paths, it
# should read `${HARNESS_ROOT_PACKAGE}` from this file rather than hardcode
# the template's base package. `scripts/harness/test-hooks` already wires
# per-fixture `harness.env` overrides through to the hook dispatcher so
# such a hook can be regression-tested with alternate base packages.
#
# FORKERS: edit the value below to match your own base package, e.g.
#   HARNESS_ROOT_PACKAGE=com/example/acme
HARNESS_ROOT_PACKAGE=nl/jinsoo/template
